{
  "text_id": "oracc.etcsri.Q000992",
  "corpus": "oracc",
  "title": "Šu-Suen 03 (RIME 3/2.01.04.03 composite)",
  "language": "sumerian",
  "translation_source": "ORACC ETCSRI — CC BY-SA 3.0",
  "source_url": "https://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/etcsri/Q000992",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Enlil , the king of all lands , his master ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.30",
      "line_range": "30",
      "translation": "(iv 2) Even the young men who evaded the battle and took refuge like birds in their cities could not escape his hand . He shrieked at their cities like an Anzu-bird . He reduced their cities and settlements to ruin mounds . He destroyed their walls completely ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.43",
      "line_range": "43",
      "translation": "(iv 15) He blinded all the young men of the cities he had conquered , and made them serve in the orchards of Enlil and Ninlil and in the orchards of the great gods ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.51",
      "line_range": "51",
      "translation": "(iv 23) He presented the female workers of the cities he conquered to the textile mills of Enlil and Ninlil and to the temples of the great gods ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.60",
      "line_range": "60",
      "translation": "(iv 32) He offered all the cattle , sheep , and the animals that he ... in the temple of Enlil and Ninlil , and in the temple of the great gods ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.67",
      "line_range": "67",
      "translation": "(v 5) He filled numerous big leather sacks with gold , silver , nir - stone , and ..... He loaded copper and tin , and items fashioned from bronze on numerous pack-asses . He donated ( all these items ) to the temple of Enlil and Ninlil , and to the temple of the great gods eternally ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.83",
      "line_range": "83",
      "translation": "(vi 19) Then Šu-Suen , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters , fashioned his own statue from the gold of the Šimaškian lands taken by him as booty . He dedicated it to Enlil , his master , for his well-being ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.98",
      "line_range": "98",
      "translation": "(vi 34) Whoever gives order to perform a misdeed against this ( statue ) , erases its inscription and writes his own name on it , destroys handiwork , may Enlil , the lord of all lands , Ninlil , the lady of all gods , curse this man !"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.112",
      "line_range": "112",
      "translation": "(vii 13) May Ninurta , the powerful warrior of Enlil , be the commissioner of this ( curse ) !"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.117",
      "line_range": "117",
      "translation": "(colophon 1, 17) The inscription on its socle ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000992.120",
      "line_range": "120",
      "translation": "(caption 1, 19) Šu-Suen , the king whom Enlil chose with the love of his heart as the shepherd of the Land and of the four quarters , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters ."
    }
  ],
